main event: A citizen observed 2 objects, one larger than the other, hovering over the moon.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on September 2, 1963, at 1630 local time., The objects were stationary and viewed through 8x binoculars., The observer speculated that the objects might be Jupiter and one of its satellites., The moon was positioned at an azimuth of 229 degrees and altitude of 15.13., The sighting lasted approximately 10 seconds.
sighted object: two unidentified objects hovering over the moon
